article.headline: Murray State 68, Delaware State 39
article.story: MURRAY, Ky (AP) -- Charles Johnson and Keith Jenifer led a balanced Murray State attack Wednesday night as the Racers beat Delaware State 68-39. Johnson scored a game-high 16 points for Murray State (4-3), while Jenifer added 12 for the Racers. Delaware State (3-7) was led by Tracey Worley's 10 points. Murray State's Shawn Witherspoon scored a layup with 11:33 in the second half that started a 25-0 run and was capped off by a 3-pointer by Shane Dansby with 2:23 remaining. The Hornets were held to 17 first half points, and they shot just 30 percent for the game. Murray State connected on 27-of-51 from the field (52 percent). The Racers also forced 19 turnovers and held a 30-23 advantage on the boards.
